		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Working with Silks: High level tailors</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:blarrg@iol.com">Renalron</a> | 
		            1/4/2000 10:58:13 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Tailoring seems to have a reputation as a 'newbie craft.' However this isn't so at all. Silks are essential for casters and monks. You know that raw silk your wearing casters? That comes from the same hands that make patchwork and leather. Cured silk is a great armor for monks, and when it comes to non-magic armor, it's one of the best for monks. Raw silk items are great for mid-level casters, and they come cheap. Most tailoring, including all guides previously posted here, leave out these great crafts. Patchwork, studded leather, re-inforced leather... Well Silk is in there some where. Silk items are in high demand for mid level casters and just about all monks. You can make quite a good bit of platnium if you're skilled with silks. <BR>
     <BR>
       HOW TO MAKE SWATCHES<BR>
<BR>
 First of all you're going to need spider silk. NOT spiderling silk. Spider silk is a common drop off of giant spiders everywhere. Put two spider silks into your &lt;b&gt;large&lt;/b&gt; sewing kit(These can be bought in most sewing stores, but not all)... Now combine them. If your skill is high enough, you have created a the vital piece of silk tailoring: The silk SWATCH.<BR>
<BR>
    TURNING YOUR SWATCH INTO <BR>
           AN ITEM<BR>
Place the swatch into your large sewing kit. What do you want to make? Lets use, for example, a pair of raw silk slippers. Buy a boot patern at a sewing store. Put the patern into the sewing kit with your swatch. Now combine the two. If your skill was high enough, you now have a cool pair of raw silk slippers, and about 5-10 plat in your hand if you can find the right person, and a great item for your caster. <BR>
<BR>
        ADVANCED SILK:<BR>
         MONK ARMOR<BR>
A monk's armor is cured silk. To make this item, you will first need to make a brewing item, heady Kiola. I detail how to make this further below. Now, take a pateren, a swatch, and, depending on what item you are trying to make, a number of heady kiolas. Check the other tailoring guides for this: You will need as many heady kiolas as you need studs for studded leather armor, or bores, for re-inforced leather armor. Combine them, and if you have a high enough skill, you've made monk Cured Silk Armor.<BR>
<BR>
        EXTENTION INTO BREWING:<BR>
        HEADY KIOLA<BR>
Find a brewing cask in a city somewhere, and place into it the following: 2 packets of kiola sap, 1 water, 1 bottle.<BR>
These items can be bought at any pub/bar in Norath, but you will probably not find the Heady Kiola for sale. You'll need to make it yourself!<BR>
<BR>
        Hope this helps...questions? Im on the Povar server... Message Renalron (still working on ideas for my sur-name)<BR>
<BR>
         Thanks,<BR>
         Renalron 20th Level    Warrior, Povar server
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
